groundTruth.text:
Abstract
                Purpose
                The main aim of this study was to estimate breast cancer survival in Poland over the period from 2000 to 2019 in both sexes.
              
                Methods
                Data were obtained from the Polish National Cancer Registry. The presented metrics included age-standardized 5- and 10-year net survival (NS), median survival times, years of life lost (YLLs), and standardized mortality ratios (SMRs).
              
                Results
                Between 2000 and 2019, 315,278 patients (2353 men and 312,925 women; male-to-female ratio 1/100) were diagnosed with breast cancer in Poland. In this period, 721,987 YLLs were linked to breast cancer. Women presented a higher 5- and 10-year age-standardized NS than men (5-year NS: 77.33% for women and 65.47% for men, P < 0.001, common language effect size (CL) 1.00; 10-year NS: 68.75% for women and 49.50% for men, P < 0.001, CL 1.00). Between the earliest and latest studied period, namely 2000–2004 and 2015–2019, there was a statistically significant increase only in female survival (+ 7.32 pp, P < 0.001, CL 1.00). SMRs were significantly higher for women than for men (3.35 vs. 2.89, respectively).
              
                Conclusion
                Over the last two decades, breast cancer survival in Poland has improved significantly. Nonetheless, special attention should be given to the disparities between sexes and the gap in overall improvement of survival rates compared with other European countries.

templateData.title: Technical Framework for Analyzing Sex-Specific Cancer Survival Disparities
templateData.description: A bioinformatics research template emphasizing computational methodologies, quantitative metrics, and technical configurations for investigating sex-based disparities in cancer survival outcomes using multi-omics and clinical data integration

templateProperty.label: Primary Multi-Omics Dataset
templateProperty.description: Named dataset(s) containing matched genomic, transcriptomic, and clinical data with sex-disaggregated survival outcomes (e.g., TCGA, UK Biobank, or custom cohorts). Must include sample size per sex and data modalities.

templateProperty.label: Confounder Adjustment Methodology
templateProperty.description: Technical approach for adjusting socioeconomic/biological confounders (e.g., propensity score matching, stratified Cox regression, or deep learning-based domain adaptation). Include mathematical formulation and software tools (e.g., `R::survival`, `Python::lifelines`).

templateProperty.label: Survival Analysis Model Architecture
templateProperty.description: Specific model architecture used (e.g., Cox-PH, Random Survival Forest, DeepSurv, or neural networks with time-to-event loss). Include hyperparameters (e.g., layers, learning rate) and framework (e.g., `PyTorch`, `TensorFlow Survival`).

templateProperty.label: Sex-Stratified Performance Metric
templateProperty.description: Primary quantitative metric for evaluating disparities (e.g., ΔC-index, hazard ratio disparity, or AUC difference between sexes). Must include statistical test (e.g., log-rank p-value) and threshold for significance.

templateProperty.label: Sex-Biased Feature Selection Technique
templateProperty.description: Computational method for identifying sex-specific biomarkers (e.g., LASSO, Boruta, or autoencoder-based feature importance). Specify tools (e.g., `scikit-learn`, `DESeq2`) and criteria for sex-differential selection.

templateProperty.label: Reproducibility Package
templateProperty.description: Named computational environment or container (e.g., Docker image, Conda YAML, or Renku project) with exact dependencies for replication. Must include versioned tools (e.g., `R 4.3.0`, `Python 3.10`).

templateProperty.label: Cross-Validation Scheme
templateProperty.description: Technical details of validation (e.g., 5-fold stratified CV, leave-one-center-out, or nested CV) with explicit handling of sex imbalance (e.g., stratified sampling). Report mean ± SD of primary metric across folds.

templateProperty.label: External Benchmark Dataset URL
templateProperty.description: Link to an independent dataset (e.g., METABRIC, ICGC) used for external validation of sex-specific findings. Must include DOI or stable repository URL.

templateProperty.label: Peak Computational Runtime
templateProperty.description: Wall-clock time (in hours) and hardware specs (e.g., GPU/TPU type, CPU cores) for the most resource-intensive step (e.g., model training or feature selection). Report as mean ± SD across 3 runs.
